  section#workflow.solid
    div.main-wrapper
      div.trigger
      div.section-split
        div.section-left
          div.section-text-wrapper
            h2 Crazy fast workflow
        div.section-right
          p We’ve paid special attention to making Streamline faster and easier to use than ever before.
          p Drop these icons right into your workflow without skipping a beat, no matter which software or file format you prefer.

          div.section-right-content

            //- software section
            div.section-right-container
              img(src="_assets/img/screenshots/iconjar.png" alt="iconjar screenshot of desktop app showing grid of icons and navigation")
              div.software-description
                img.app-icon(src="_assets/img/screenshots/iconjar.svg" alt="icon jar icon — blue bottle with a drip")
                h3 IconJar
                p One of the easiest ways to use the icons, if you're on a Mac. Open the <code>.iconjar</code> file and you have a beautifully organized list of every section and subsection. In addition, you can simply search for any icon by name and it will appear instantly. Drag and drop the vector icon straight from IconJar into your favorite design software. It just works.

            //- software section
            div.section-right-container
              img(src="_assets/img/screenshots/sketch.png" alt="sketch screenshot")
              div.software-description
                img.app-icon(src="_assets/img/screenshots/sketch.svg" alt="sketch icon")
                h3 Sketch
                p Each category of icon comes with its very own <code>.sketch</code> file. The icons have been pre-made into 24x24 symbols, meticulously named and organized for you. Works great with Sketch Runner and symbol overrides in general. Using these icons in Sketch has never been easier.

            //- software section
            div.section-right-container
              img(src="_assets/img/screenshots/figma.png" alt="figma screenshot")
              div.software-description
                img.app-icon(src="_assets/img/screenshots/figma.svg" alt="figma icon")
                h3 Figma
                p Figma opens Sketch files pretty flawlessly, but we went ahead and did the dirty work for you by converting the same Sketch icon category files into nice and tidy <code>.fig</code> files. You're welcome. Fun fact: Vincent and Matt used Figma to design this website.

            //- software section
            div.section-right-container
              img(src="_assets/img/screenshots/studio.png" alt="studio screenshot")
              div.software-description
                img.app-icon(src="_assets/img/screenshots/studio.svg" alt="studio icon")
                h3 Studio (Coming Soon)
                p We've ran some initial tests on converting our <code>.sketch</code> files into <code>.studio</code> files. The results are very promising and as soon as Studio is out of beta, our official files will be ready too.

            //- software section
            div.section-right-container
              img(src="_assets/img/screenshots/illustrator.png" alt="illustrator screenshot")
              div.software-description
                img.app-icon(src="_assets/img/screenshots/illustrator.svg" alt="illustrator icon")
                h3 Illustrator
                p Ahh, old faithful. The grandfather of all vector editing software. You can bet your bottom dollar we've got a bunch of <code>.ai</code> files for all of you Adobe fans out there.

            //- software section
            div.section-right-container
              img(src="_assets/img/screenshots/svg.png" alt="code editor screenshot showing svg code")
              div.software-description
                img.app-icon(src="_assets/img/screenshots/svg.svg" alt="svg icon")
                h3 SVG
                p SVGee whiz. We spent a lot of time converting all of these icons into clean code for all of the developers out there. All of the hard-coded HEX codes have been refactored to <code>currentColor</code> and the markup has been stripped down to the bare essentials.


            div.section-right-container
              blockquote
                p “Vincent's icons are unique, versatile, and easy to work with. I've found them to be super useful across a range of projects.”
                footer
